prompts.prompt: Develop a minimalist web page featuring a central logo at the top, followed by a prominent search bar. Below the search bar, include two buttons resembling Google's 'Search' and 'I'm Feeling Lucky' buttons, with customizable text options. Incorporate a footer at the bottom of the page containing links for company information, privacy, and settings. Optionally, add a top right corner section with customizable links for services similar to Google's 'Gmail' and 'Images', and a grid icon for additional services. Ensure the entire page design is responsive to adapt seamlessly to different screen sizes and devices for optimal user experience.

Develop a minimalist web page with a central logo using the image from 'https://source.unsplash.com/random'. Below the logo, place a prominent search bar. When a user enters a query and clicks the search button, display a 'Thank You' message on the UI. Include two buttons below the search bar resembling Google's 'Search' and 'I'm Feeling Lucky', with customizable text. Add a footer containing links for company information, privacy, and settings. Optionally, incorporate a top right corner section with customizable links for services and a grid icon for more services. The design should be responsive to adapt to different screen sizes and devices.

Below the logo, place a prominent search bar. When a user enters a query and clicks the search button, display a 'Thank You' message on the UI. Modify the existing web page to include a configuration in the next.config.js file for remotePatterns. This configuration will allow the web page to fetch the Google logo image ('https://www.google.com/images/branding/googlelogo/2x/googlelogo_color_272x92dp.png') from an external source rather than from within the generated code directory. Ensure the rest of the web page design remains the same, with a central logo, a search bar, two buttons, a responsive design, and a footer with links.
